Package com.cafean.client.analysis

Class ComponentSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.analysis.ComponentSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<AbstractComponent>, java.util.Collection<AbstractComponent>
    public class ComponentSet
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Collection<AbstractComponent>
    A set of components that can be searched and traversed as a full set or by category, ident, component number, etc..

    Access to specific component types by category can be optimized by "partitioning" the set by these categories. Refer to addPartitions(Category...) for a more detailed description.

    Implementation notes:

    1) resetCache() should be called any time the category structure or presence changes in a plug-in. Extensions of StreamModel can do this as part of their implementation of the fireModelChanged().

    2) Plug-ins that make use of the component set (instead of the legacy ComponentList) should, for efficiency, override
    AbstractModel.getComponents() with:

    return model.components().toArray(new AbstractComponent[0]);

    and AbstractModel.getComponentCount() with:

    return model.components().size();

    3) addPartitions(Category...) should be used to speed access to frequently traversed categories. The following snippet is often sufficient. Note, however, that if the plug-in includes components that are not displayed in the Navigator, those categories should be added explicitly.

    model.components().addPartitions(model.getCategories());

    See Also:
    addPartitions(com.cafean.client.analysis.Category...), resetCache()

      • stream

        public java.util.stream.Stream<AbstractComponent> stream​(Category... categories)
        Returns a stream of the components in this list that are in a sub-set of one or more of the given categories.

        Note that if the given categories are part of a single partition then the stream will be a single traversal of that partition. If they are not part of a single partition then the available components will be traversed once for each of the given categories.

        WARNING: Unless the given categories are in a single partition, no attempt will be made to eliminate duplicates from the resulting stream. If the given categories are overlapping then the stream will include the overlapped components more than once. Consider either using non-overlapping categories, an explicit filter with a single traversal of the entire list using stream().filter(...), or collecting the results into a set.

        Parameters:
        categories - a Category[] containing the desired categories
        Returns:
        a Stream containing the desired components.

      • resetCache

        public void resetCache()
        Updates and/or recalculates all caching used to speed access to components in this set. This method should be called any time a model's list of categories or their structure is changed.

        WARNING: The list of categories used as partitions in this set will not be changed when calling this method.

        See Also:
        addPartitions(Category...)

      • addPartitions

        public void addPartitions​(Category... categories)
                   throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
        Adds the given categories to the set of partitioned categories. Partitioned categories are sub-sets of the full component lists that are frequently traversed by category. Categories that are often filtered and listed separately from the rest of the components in the model should be added here.

        Note: Partition categories that overlap (i.e. subsets of one another) are not allowed. Attempting to add overlapping partition categories will result in an UnsupportedOperationException.

        Parameters:
        categories - a Category[] containing the categories to optimize.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if any of the given categories overlap each other or other categories already being used as partitions.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if a given category is a SearchCategory.
        See Also:
        resetCache()

      • containedInPartition

        public boolean containedInPartition​(Category category)
        Returns true if the given category is represented by or contained in a partition. This method is typically used to determine whether a given category is contained in the component set or whether a plug-in uses the component set at all.
        Parameters:
        category - the Category to search for
        Returns:
        true if the given category is in a partition.
        See Also:
        addPartitions(com.cafean.client.analysis.Category...)
